# View Styling Guidelines

## No Tailwind Utility Classes

This project does NOT use Tailwind CSS. Never add utility classes like `flex`, `p-4`, `text-gray-500`, `bg-white`, etc. to view templates.

## BEM Naming Convention

All CSS classes follow the BEM (Block Element Modifier) methodology:

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Block | `.block-name` | `.article-card` |
| Element | `.block-name__element` | `.article-card__title` |
| Modifier | `.block-name--modifier` | `.btn--primary` |

### Naming Rules

- Use lowercase with hyphens for multi-word names
- Blocks describe the component (noun): `article-card`, `comment`, `btn`
- Elements describe the part: `__title`, `__content`, `__actions`
- Modifiers describe variation: `--primary`, `--danger`, `--narrow`

## CSS File Organization

Create one CSS file per component in `app/assets/stylesheets/`:

```
app/assets/stylesheets/
├── application.css
├── page_layout.css      # .page, .page-header, .back-link
├── button.css           # .btn and modifiers
├── form.css             # .form, .form-field, .form-errors
├── article_card.css     # .article-card
├── article_detail.css   # .article-detail, .comments-section
├── comment.css          # .comment
├── comment_form.css     # .comment-form
├── empty_state.css      # .empty-state
└── publication_toggle.css
```

## Exemplar Pattern

Reference `publication_toggle.css` and `publications/_toggle.html.erb` as the canonical example:

```css
/* Block */
.publication-toggle {
  display: inline-block;
}

/* Element */
.publication-toggle__button {
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  /* ... */
}

/* Modifiers */
.publication-toggle__button--publish {
  background-color: #16a34a;
}

.publication-toggle__button--unpublish {
  background-color: #d97706;
}
```

```erb
<div class="publication-toggle">
  <%= button_to "Publish", path, class: "publication-toggle__button publication-toggle__button--publish" %>
</div>
```

## Available Blocks

### Layout
- `.page` - Page container with centered content (modifiers: `--narrow`, `--medium`)
- `.page-header` - Page title + action area
- `.back-link` - Navigation back link

### Components
- `.btn` - Buttons (modifiers: `--primary`, `--secondary`, `--danger`, `--link`, `--link-danger`)
- `.article-card` - Article listing card
- `.article-detail` - Article show page
- `.comment` - Single comment display
- `.empty-state` - Empty state message

### Forms
- `.form` - Form container
- `.form-field` - Single form field wrapper
- `.form-errors` - Error message box
- `.form-actions` - Form button container
- `.comment-form` - Comment-specific form

## Adding New Components

1. Create a new CSS file: `app/assets/stylesheets/component_name.css`
2. Define the block and its elements/modifiers
3. Use semantic class names that describe purpose, not appearance
4. Add hover/focus states with `transition` for smooth effects
